        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 31 at 8:33PM MDT by NWS Goodland KS</headline>
        <description>At 833 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from 3 miles west of Sedgwick to 5 miles north of
Lone Star to 7 miles southwest of Burdett. Movement was southeast at
30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

These storms will remain over mainly rural areas of northwestern Yuma
County, including the following locations... Clarkville.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
